HEADWORD: Brumaire
<hw>Bru`maire"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>bruma</ets> winter.]</ety> <def>The second month of the calendar
adopted by the first French republic. It began thirty days after the
autumnal equinox. See <er>Vendemiaire</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

